Embu Senator Lenny Kivuti yesterday advised landlords in low- cost residential areas to avoid installing power on their premises without involving Kenya Power.He said many houses are razed by fires owing to faulty connections by unqualified people. Kivuti said Kenya Power experts will greatly reduce accidental fires.He spoke at Dallas estate, when he consoled 23 families made homeless after their houses were razed by a fire on Saturday afternoon. Kivuti donated Sh110,000, as they seek permanent quarters.The families did not salvage anything and were left with the clothes they were wearing. They appealed to well-wishers to come to their aid.